RAMESH LAXMAN PARDESHI V. STATE OF MAHARASHTRA [1987] INSC 101; 1987 (2) SCR 907; 1987 Suppl.SCC 1; 1987 (3) JT 5; 1987 (1) SCALE 826 (10 April 1987)

 OZA, G.L. (J) OZA, G.L. (J) KHALID, V. (J) 
CITATION: 1987 SCR (2) 907 [1987] INSC 101; 1987 SCC Supl. 1 JT 1987 (3) 5 1987 SCALE (1)826 
ACT:
 Indian Penal Code, 1860--S. 302 or 304 Part I--Evidence indicated exchange of hot words--Prosecution Witnesses deliberately suppressed the exact words used--Whether infer- ence could be drawn that if those words were given out, it would have damaged the prosecution case--Whether the words used by the deceased and his friends caused provocation to accused--No premeditation--Injury caused at spur of moment and in heat of passion proved fatal--Whether intention to cause death can be attributed--Whether the case would fall within the purview of s. 302 or 304 Part I.
 
